incident_updates.body: Start time : 05/03/2024 11:20 UTC Service impact : Some websites slowness on cluster031 Root cause : Overload on compute equipments Ongoing actions : Monitoring

Start time : 05/03/2024 11:20 UTC Service impact : Some websites slowness on cluster031 Ongoing actions : Our technical teams are investigating the issue. Update will be posted as significant progress is made.

Some of the sms affected by the incident have not yet received their acknowledgements of receipt. 
Our teams are working to reintegrate the sms whose acknowledgements of receipt are still in error. 
Update will be posted as significant progress is made.

Our provider implemented the definitive patch and fixed the issue.
SMS received by the customers have their status updated to delivered.
Our teams are currently working on integrating the delivered status that has not been received.
The patch that has been implemented has considerably reduced the impact and DLRs (delivery reporting) are in the process of being inserted.

Start time : 23/02/2024 17:15 UTC Service impact : Customers are receiving SMS but some SMS delivery status is not updated as delivered Ongoing actions : Our technical teams are currently working with our provider to solve the issue. Update will be posted as significant progress is made.

The technical incident was resolved on 08/02.
Tickets that were not counted are gradually being refunded.

Our teams are continuing to work on a fix for this issue.
Update will be post as significant progress is made.

Our teams are working tirelessly to resolve this incident once and for all.
Update will be post as significant progress is made.

Our technical teams are still processing the previous months. 
Processing for October and November is now completed.
The processing of past months is in progress, that of October is completed.
Update : Our technical team is working on resolving the billing issue for the month of October 2023. We are continuing to work on a fix for this issue.

Update : A fix has been implemented and is now working, next calls will be billed correctly. The new tickets are good and will be refunded. As for the tickets that have not been counted since the start of the incident, we are working to reintegrate them, but this is still in progress.
We are continuing to work on a fix for this issue.
We are continuing to work on a fix for this issue.
The issue has been identified and a fix is being implemented.

Start time : 24/10/2023 12:00 UTC Service impact : Customer having french Value-Added Service (+338xxxxxxxx) plugged on OVH Call Queue or OVH Contact Centre Solution have missing calls for payout. Root cause : Migration on internal routing. Ongoing actions : Our team are working to fix the issue.

As part of our continuous improvement plan, maintenance is scheduled on our web cloud offer. This may temporarily affect the availability for the log service. Start time : 06/03/2024 13:00 UTC End time : 06/03/2024 13:10 UTC Service impact : Reroute DynDNS calls Service improvement : Following our continuous improvement policy, we will upgrade the DynDNS service. Thank you for your understanding.

Start time : 06/03/2024 18:00 UTC End time : 06/03/2024 23:00 UTC Service impact : All projects and environments will continue to function during the upgrade; however, at one point, a short downtime of no more than 10 minutes will be experienced. Integrations and webhooks may fail during the maintenance, and you may notice increased deployment times Service improvement : Our partner communicated to OVHCloud that they will be doing a routine maintenance on account service. This maintenance is expected to not have impact on the projects: no downtime, no performance issue are expected.
